               stealing, on the <rs id="t18240916-242-cd1291" type="crimeDate">2d of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240916-242-off1290 t18240916-242-cd1291"></join>, a carpenter's plough, value 5 s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t18240916-242-victim2023" type="victimName">
                     John 
                     Hart
                  <interp inst="t18240916-242-victim2023" type="surname" value="Hart"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-242-victim2023" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-242-victim2023" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240916-242-off1290 t18240916-242-victim2023"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>JOHN HART. I am a <rs id="t18240916-242-viclabel1292" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240916-242-victim2023 t18240916-242-viclabel1292"></join>. I had a plough stolen from a new house which I was building, in <placeName id="t18240916-242-crimeloc1293">Hertford-road, Hackney</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18240916-242-crimeloc1293" type="placeName" value="Hertford-road, Hackney"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18240916-242-crimeloc1293" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240916-242-off1290 t18240916-242-crimeloc1293"></join>; I had lent it some time before to Powel. I saw it again at the office on the 7th or 8th of 
               <persName id="t18240916-242-person2024">August.</persName>
             The prisoner had been in my employ, but not at that time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-242-person2025">
                  JOSEPH 
                  CARTER
               <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2025" type="surname" value="CARTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2025" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2025" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am apprentice to Mr. Hart. His plough was at the building, being used by one of the men; I saw it their on Monday morning, the 2d of August; it was missed after dinner, when the men came to work. I saw the prisoner at the lower part of the house that morning, between eleven and twelve o'clock; he was known to the workmen. I saw the plough at the pawnbroker's on the Wednesday following.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-242-person2026">
                  JOSEPH 
                  POWELL
               <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2026" type="surname" value="POWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2026" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2026" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Mr. Hart's employ. I had used this plough in the morning; we went to dinner at twelve o'clock; I left the plough up stairs. We returned at one, but I did not miss it till about three; I saw it again at the office, and knew it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-242-person2027">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HENRY MILLS
               <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2027" type="surname" value="HENRY MILLS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2027" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2027" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker, and live with Mr. Hewit, of Kingsland-road. I took in this plough, which was afterwards claimed by Mr. Hart, on Monday, the 2d of August; about twelve o'clock. The house from which it was said to be taken, is about half a mile from our shop. I am quite certain it was brought by the prisoner; I lent him 3 s. on it.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Do you recollect my dress - A. A pair of blue trowsers, black waistcoat, and fustian jacket. He was in the same dress when at the office.</p>
               <p>Prisoner to 
               <persName id="t18240916-242-person2028">
                  JOSEPH 
                  CARTER
               <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2028" type="surname" value="CARTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2028" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2028" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Q. On the day you saw me at the building what clothes had I on - A. The same dress as the pawnbroker has described, only he had a blue coat over his fustian jacket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-242-person2029">
                  GEORGE 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2029" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2029" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-242-person2029" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner was brought to the watch-house on Thursday night - he was dressed to the best of my recollection as the pawnbroker has described.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been talking to the carpenter at the building, but I had a different dress to what has been stated.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 45.</p>
               <p>
